description: If any power of 2 ends with k 3's and 4's, they must be the first k elements of this sequence in reverse order.
comments: Conjecture: a(n) = 3rd divisor of smallest number having exactly n+2 divisors, a(n)=T(n+2,3), T as defined in A081532. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jul 18 2003
author: _David W. Wilson_
